List of Necessary functions

Frontend

- Dashboard - Page that allows to quickly see what information is stored.
- Entry page - Page that allows the entry of food information + price
- Stock page - Tracks total amount of each item used
- Data page - Allow people to see all of their tracked information on a day by day basis

-- Required "Cards"
   - Dash
     Macro tracking "wheels"
     Calorie tracking -> Current and Goal
     Total calories in stock
     Notifications box
     
   - Entry
     Food information insertion + Price + Wastage
     Meal insertion + Calculated cost
     Meal picker
     Track loss
     
   - Stock
     Total calories remaining
     Total calories of each macro
     
   - Data view
     Breakdown stock usage per meal per day
     Show total calories and macros for each meal and for each day

   - Notifications
     Notifications have a title, alert level and body
     They report information such as too few calories or too much.

- Custom CSS style for interface

Backend

- Food insertion
  Somehow, basic food + its cost should be inserted and then tracked by Stock page
  The main macros to focus on are Fat, Protien and Carbohydrates
  This data could come either from nutrition labels with image processing or maybe manual insertion - If it has to be manual, notify Frontend
  Price could also come from the same - maybe give items a number of aliases for mass trackign

- Stock manager
  The stock manager tags all inserted food
  A food item must have
    Primary Name
    Reciept Alias
    Price
    Fat
    Protein
    Carbs
  The stock manager should keep tally of how much of each item a person has
      - It should keep track in grams and in units
      - It should keep track of how much total calories are there - send notification
      - It should keep track of how many total of each macro there is - send notification

- Data processing
  Image recognition - Unnecessary
    A function that can extract the text from a receipt or a nutrition label, and pick the necessary values
      - This is definitely the hardest part but i think Python has some OCR library
    Once this data is found, The relevant details are extracted (Macros, calories for the food, and Price per unit/Per weight for reciept)
    The name on the reciept is then tied to the nutrition information and the size/weight of the pack, and then this is sent to Stock
    
- Calorie processing
    - Sum total calories
    - Sum calories from each macro
    - Check calories and macros against goal amounts - send notification
    - Compute over/under and check if significantly low - send notification
    - Compare calorie intake and weight over time

- Price computation
  -  compute cost of meals and total cost per day


Data exchange formats

Dashboard -> Expects payload
	  {Total Calories,
	  Goal Calories,
	  Total Fat, Goal Fat
	  Total Protien, Goal Protein,
	  Total Carbs, Goal Carbs
	  Total calories in stock,
	  Notifications}


Food item creation -> Expects
     	  {Food Item Name,
	  Reciept Allias,
	  Price,
	  Unit size/ Weight,
	  Calories per 100,
	  Fat per 100,
	  Protien per 100,
	  Carbs per 100}

Reciept lookup -> Takes {Receipt Name, Price, Qty}
	       Lookup Name in Alliases
	       Add Qty of that item to stock
	       Add in price

Stock List -> Return everything in food item object where qty > 0